spec: agent-core.ai-docs/v1
namespace: "Application\\Handler"
fqcn: "Ineersa\\AgentCore\\Application\\Handler"
updatedAt: 2026-04-19
description: "Handler infrastructure — command routing, extension registries, LLM/tool execution workers, outbox projectors, event dispatching, step dispatch, locking, idempotency, replay, tool batch collection, bounded parallel dispatch, and idempotency result store."
files[21]{file,type,summary}:
  RunEventDispatcher.php,readonly final class,This class acts as a facade for dispatching specific run-related events within the agent core application. It encapsulates the interaction between a subscriber registry and a generic event dispatcher to ensure proper event routing.
  ToolBatchCollectOutcome.php,readonly final class,"A value object representing the outcome of a batch tool execution within the agent core. It encapsulates execution status flags, ordered results, and pending effects to ensure immutable state representation."
  ToolExecutor.php,final class,"The ToolExecutor class orchestrates the safe and efficient execution of tool calls within an agent's runtime environment. It manages policy resolution, argument validation, idempotency caching, and integration with external toolboxes like Symfony."
  MessageIdempotencyService.php,final class,This class manages idempotency for agent execution runs by tracking unique operation keys within specific scopes. It prevents duplicate processing of identical requests by checking for prior existence and recording new completions. The design ensures that repeated invocations with the same key are safely ignored after the first successful execution.
  EventSubscriberRegistry.php,final class,"This class manages a registry of event subscribers, allowing for efficient retrieval of handlers associated with specific event types. It acts as a central dispatcher lookup mechanism within the agent core application."
  ToolCatalogResolver.php,final class,"This class resolves tool definitions from registered providers, ensuring schema consistency across the agent core. It aggregates provider payloads and validates that tool schemas remain stable during resolution."
  ToolExecutionResultStore.php,final class,This class provides a storage mechanism for caching tool execution results within an agent core system. It supports retrieval by run context or by idempotency keys to prevent redundant tool executions.
  ExecuteToolCallWorker.php,readonly final class,This class acts as a message handler for executing tool calls within an agent's execution pipeline. It coordinates the invocation of specific tools and manages the resulting state updates via a command bus. The design separates tool execution logic from message handling to ensure clean separation of concerns.
  ExecuteLlmStepWorker.php,readonly final class,This class acts as a message handler for executing LLM steps within the agent execution pipeline. It coordinates with the platform to retrieve necessary context and dispatches commands via a dedicated message bus. The handler processes incoming execution messages and returns structured results.
  OutboxProjector.php,readonly final class,"This class processes domain events from an outbox store to update application state and publish resulting events. It coordinates the retrieval of pending events, their execution via a run log, and the subsequent publication of new events."
  HookSubscriberRegistry.php,final class,"This class manages a registry of hook subscribers, allowing efficient retrieval of handlers associated with specific hook names. It acts as a central dispatcher for event-driven logic within the agent core application."
  ReplayService.php,readonly final class,ReplayService reconstructs the prompt state for a given run by replaying historical events from the event store. It ensures data integrity and calculates token estimates for the reconstructed message history.
  StepDispatcher.php,readonly final class,The StepDispatcher class acts as a mediator for executing side-effects and publishing domain events within the agent core application. It decouples business logic from message transport by routing operations to specific message buses. This design ensures that effects and publications are handled through standardized interfaces.
  CommandHandlerRegistry.php,final class,"This class acts as a centralized registry for command handlers, mapping specific command kinds to their corresponding handler implementations. It provides a lookup mechanism to retrieve the appropriate handler for a given command type at runtime."
  ToolBatchCollector.php,final class,"The ToolBatchCollector aggregates tool calls into batches based on run, turn, and step identifiers, enforcing parallelism limits. It manages the lifecycle of pending tool calls by registering expected batches and collecting results to determine when a batch is complete."
  CommandRouter.php,final class,The CommandRouter class acts as a central dispatcher that maps incoming ApplyCommand instances to their corresponding handler implementations. It leverages a CommandHandlerRegistry to resolve handlers based on command metadata and validates command options against a configurable extension prefix.
  RunLockManager.php,readonly final class,"Manages distributed execution locks for agent runs to prevent concurrent processing. It uses a factory to acquire locks with a configurable time-to-live, ensuring thread-safe execution of critical sections."
  HookDispatcher.php,readonly final class,The HookDispatcher acts as a central mediator that resolves registered hook subscribers and triggers their execution. It coordinates the interaction between the subscriber registry and the event dispatcher to ensure hooks are invoked with the provided context.
  MercureOutboxProjectorWorker.php,readonly final class,This class processes Mercure outbox messages by retrieving pending events from a store and publishing them via a dedicated event publisher. It acts as a worker that bridges the outbox persistence layer with the runtime event distribution mechanism.
  JsonlOutboxProjectorWorker.php,readonly final class,This class processes JSONL outbox messages by persisting them to the configured outbox store and recording execution details in the run log. It acts as a dedicated handler for asynchronous event projection tasks within the agent core application.
  ToolExecutionPolicyResolver.php,readonly final class,This class determines the execution policy for tools by combining a default configuration with specific overrides. It ensures consistent tool execution behavior by resolving timeout and parallelism constraints based on the requested tool name.